## Interfaces

- **Define interfaces at the consumer, not the producer.**
- Keep interfaces small. Prefer 1–3 methods.
- Accept interfaces, return concrete types.

```go
// ✅ Good — interface defined where it's used (in the service package)
type UserStore interface {
    GetByID(ctx context.Context, id int64) (*User, error)
    Save(ctx context.Context, u *User) error
}

type UserService struct {
    store UserStore
    log   *slog.Logger
}

// ❌ Bad — exporting a giant interface from the repository package
type Repository interface {
    GetUser() ...
    SaveUser() ...
    DeleteUser() ...
    ListUsers() ...
    GetOrder() ...
    // 40 more methods...
}
```

