## Context

- Always first parameter: `func DoSomething(ctx context.Context, ...)`.
- Never store context in a struct. Pass it through calls.
- Use `context.WithTimeout` at I/O boundaries, not deep in the stack.
- Store only request-scoped values: trace IDs, auth tokens. Not config or loggers.

```go
// ✅ Good
ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 5*time.Second)
defer cancel()
result, err := db.QueryContext(ctx, query)

// ❌ Bad — storing ctx in struct
type Service struct {
    ctx context.Context // never do this
}
```

