## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

| Pitfall | Fix |
|---|---|
| Goroutine leak | Always cancel context or close channel |
| `nil` map write panic | Initialize with `make(map[K]V)` |
| Loop variable capture (pre-1.22) | Copy `item := item` inside loop |
| Ignoring errors | Always handle — at minimum log and return |
| Using `init()` for side effects | Use explicit initialization in `main` |
| Panic in library code | Return errors instead |
| Naked returns | Name returns only when genuinely clarifying |
| Over-using global state | Inject dependencies explicitly |
| Premature optimization | Profile first with `pprof`, then optimize |
| Large interface | Split into focused interfaces |

