## Module Management

```bash
# Initialize
go mod init github.com/org/project

# Add dependency
go get github.com/some/package@v1.2.3

# Upgrade all
go get -u ./...

# Remove unused
go mod tidy

# Vendor (optional, for reproducible builds)
go mod vendor
```

Keep `go.sum` committed. Use `go mod tidy` before every commit.

---

## Performance Guidelines

- Avoid allocations in hot paths — use `sync.Pool` for reusable objects.
- Prefer `[]byte` over `string` for I/O-heavy code.
- Pre-size slices/maps when length is known: `make([]T, 0, n)`.
- Use `strings.Builder` for string concatenation in loops.
- Profile before optimizing: `go test -bench=. -cpuprofile=cpu.out`, then `go tool pprof`.
- Use `go build -gcflags="-m"` to inspect escape analysis.

